    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-07-01T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-07-01T09:00:00-05:00" n="521"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d521">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/13357: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Swatow</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Young</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Swatow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-07-01T22:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 1, 1938—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 2—7 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>From 4:30 to 6 p.m., 9 Japanese bombers dropped 71 bombs without warning
                    indiscriminately on various parts of Swatow causing <pb facs="0395" n="391"
                        xml:id="pg_391"/> probably 50 deaths among Chinese and unknown number
                    wounded. Father William J. Downs, American of Maryknoll Mission, slightly
                    wounded and his house demolished; no other American casualties.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Young</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
